                Perfect Writer Three-Key Commands

C--X  2		Make 2 windows
C--X  O		Move to other window
C--X  1		Make 1 window (i.e. close window where cursor is not)
C--X  ^		Enlarge this window (default = 4 lines)
               
C--X  <		Unallotted (contrary to Peopletalk manual 4-31) 
C--X  ,		Unallotted (contrary to Peopletalk manual 4-31)

C--X  S		Save file to disc (customized same as C--X C--S)
C--X  M		Change Mode (Save/Fill/Overwrite/Normal)

C--X  I		Insert (another) file (in this one)
C--X  =		Find line number in file's total length
C--X  R		Write Region (from previous Mark Set to this point)

C--X  B		Summon Buffer (name)
C--X  K		Kill Buffer
C--X  \		Delete trailing whitespace throughout document
		
	Next four follow ESC ## to set column desired
C--X  Tab	Reset Tabs
C--X  >		) Set Indent Column 
C--X  .		) = reset left margin
C--X  F         Set Fill Column i.e. reset right margin
	Preceding two set current cursor position, if no ESC ##

C--X  ?		Call Help File	)  Disabled in DJCP
C--X  1         Quit Help File  )  custom version

ESC C--L	Realign to mid-screen (same as ESC & Right Arrow)
