			COPY and MOVE
COPY REGION	1. Mark front of region with ESC SPACE
	   	2. At end of region type:  ESC W
		3. Position cursor at destination and type: Ctrl Y
WRITE REGION:   Complete steps 1 and 2 above and then enter:
		Ctrl X R {echo line asks for file to write region to}


			      Notes

1.   In Perfect Writer and Perfect Filer commands using
alphabetical keys work the same in upper or lower case.   (In
Perfect Calc, certain Control-- commands work only in lower
case.)

2.   Control character sets left 3 bits to 0: i.e. C--A = ^A = 0000001

